I"<p>The <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/second-brain-has-a-cognitive-architecture">second brain architecture</a> closely resembles modern human cognitive architectures. For instance, <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/fluid-search-output-resembles-working-memory">fluid search output resembles working memory</a>, <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/second-brain-contents-resemble-long-term-memory">non-linear contents resemble long-term memory</a>, and <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/second-brain-buffer-is-like-short-term-memory">a transient buffer resembles short-term memory</a>. This high-fidelity alignment can enable a functional dialogue through <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/second-brain-architecture-guides-cognitive-augmentation">guidelines for cognitive augmentation</a>. Whatâ€™s more, this close resemblence might have not been a mere coincidence, but the aggregate result of tweaking a note-taking setup in subtle intuitive ways to better <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/evolution-is-like-buying-a-suit">fit</a> human cognition. In light of this, the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/second-brain-has-a-cognitive-architecture">second brain architecture</a> is a promising research platform for AGI.</p>
